cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.AI

This paper deals with image processing tasks and machine learning methods for solving inverse problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of data-driven regularizers, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The Neumann series is a mathematical concept used in the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses optimization methods, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the use of machine learning to solve inverse problems could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
